Taobob I have to disagree with you on these points.  If it is true that everyone has something to be unhappy about then VI must be doing a hell of a good job.  It has long been recognized by professional negotiators that if you come away from an arbitration with a settlement that neither side is happy with you have probably reached the best compromise possible.  If everyone has something to be unhappy about and there are two sides (at least) to all the issues then VI must be reaching the best compromise possible.<P>This is a Massive Multiplayer game.  No matter which Multiplayer game you go to you will have these same differences of opinion.  This diversity of personality types is inevitable with Massive Multiplayers.  There is absolutely nothing that VI or anyone else can do to please all these people all the time.  They can only try to provide enough of what each person likes that it overides the things they don't like.  Make the game diverse enough that there is something for everyone.<P>Sorry, but these games are an extension of life after all.  You have real people playing these games and as such they will act as their personality in Real Life dictates.  <P>I have played RP games (a lot) with just small groups and invariably the individuals play their characters with the same personality as they exibit in RL.  They bring their selfishness or their selflessness with them to the gaming table or to the key board.  An a**hole will be an a**hole, a nice guy will be a nice guy, no changing it.<P>Jacoby Justantine<BR>Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Guild Leader of the Protectors of Harmony<BR>Saryrn Server
