Personally, I love EQ just the way it is.  It's gritty, it's frustrating, but it's also almost sickeningly rewarding to me.  I'll spend 4 hours camped somewhere with a group that can't get along to save their lives, just sitting in a corner until a creature spawns.  It can be annoying but when the fight is over and I've just dinged another level, it all seems so worth it.  The problems we're seeing with EQ aren't in the game design or in the rule setup, they're in the people who can't stop to enjoy anything for more than 3 seconds.  They always have to find something new to bitch about. <P>------------------<BR>
